VSur Sagar presents a Hindustani vocal recital by Apoorva Gokhale on July 18, Sunday.Apoorva started her music education at an early age of 5 under the tutelage of her grandfather, the late Pandit Gajananrao Joshi, who was a vocalist and violinist, reputed for his versatility and making a superb blend of three gharanas, that is Gwalior, Jaipur and Agra.She received further training under the supervision of her uncle Pandit Madhukar Joshi,a well-known vocalist and violinist and also from Pandit Ulhas Kashalkar. She currently learns from Pandit Shankar Abhyankar, the eminent sitarist and rachnakar and also from Vidushi Manik Bhide.She has been awarded with the Acharya S.N. Ratanjankar Foundation Trust's scholarship and Pandit K.G. Ginde Puraskar for two years. Apoorva has also been honoured with the titles Surmani and Sur Singar Sansad. She is an approved artist of AIR and has released a cassette and CD.Apoorva performs at The Canara Union, 8th Main, Malleshwaram Bangalore. She will be accompanied by Udayraj Karpur on tabla and Vyasmurti Katti on harmonium.***Suswaralaya will have a three-day unique youth festival Yuva Chetana to commemorate its tenth anniversary.The festival will be held on August 20, 21 and 22 at Multi Vision Theatre, ISKCON, Hare Krishna Hill, Chord Road, Bangalore.The participants will have to present a paper to be reviewed by senior musicians/musicologists/artistes and rasikas.For details write to suswaralaya@yahoo.com
